1
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:53,875
Come on…

2
00:00:54,416 --> 00:00:56,833
Don't look at me while I'm sleeping.

3
00:00:57,791 --> 00:00:58,958
Good morning.

4
00:00:59,041 --> 00:01:00,750
Don't change the subject.

5
00:01:02,333 --> 00:01:03,166
Huh?

6
00:01:05,041 --> 00:01:05,875
What?

7
00:01:06,708 --> 00:01:07,791
Did you go somewhere?

8
00:01:07,875 --> 00:01:10,708
Yeah, I went to feel the Earth a bit.

9
00:01:12,291 --> 00:01:14,291
-What?
-Can I tell you something?

10
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:19,458
I love the face you make
when you sleep, Saeko.

11
00:01:21,083 --> 00:01:21,916
Have you heard?

12
00:01:22,416 --> 00:01:26,041
If you love someone's sleeping face,
it means you'll love them forever.

13
00:01:27,541 --> 00:01:28,583
That's news to me.

14
00:01:28,666 --> 00:01:30,416
But it's true.

15
00:01:31,083 --> 00:01:34,166
And I love your face when you're asleep.

16
00:01:34,666 --> 00:01:36,291
How do I put this?

17
00:01:36,375 --> 00:01:38,708
It's almost like I prefer it.

18
00:01:39,208 --> 00:01:40,125
What?

19
00:01:40,208 --> 00:01:41,083
Sorry.

20
00:01:41,166 --> 00:01:42,416
That came out wrong.

21
00:01:42,916 --> 00:01:43,750
Oh, right.

22
00:01:44,750 --> 00:01:48,000
Hey! The sand!

23
00:01:48,083 --> 00:01:49,291
-It's fine.
-The sand!

24
00:01:49,375 --> 00:01:50,208
Come here.

25
00:01:55,583 --> 00:01:56,416
Can you feel it?

26
00:01:57,125 --> 00:01:57,958
Here.

27
00:01:58,458 --> 00:02:01,875
Can you feel the fluttering of my heart?

28
00:02:04,458 --> 00:02:05,291
I can't tell.

29
00:02:07,958 --> 00:02:10,041
That's weird.

30
00:02:11,166 --> 00:02:12,916
Oh, how about this?

31
00:02:13,791 --> 00:02:17,500
When you listen to my heartbeat,

32
00:02:18,416 --> 00:02:22,958
it's an incredibly comforting rhythm.

33
00:02:24,166 --> 00:02:25,541
It must warm you up.

34
00:02:30,333 --> 00:02:32,208
What is going on here?

35
00:02:35,750 --> 00:02:37,708
No matter how I think about it…

36
00:02:40,958 --> 00:02:43,125
you say the same things Yusuke would say.

37
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:48,125
"Yusuke"?

38
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:53,375
Yusuke Nakamachi.

39
00:02:56,958 --> 00:02:58,166
He's…

40
00:03:00,166 --> 00:03:01,666
my late partner.

41
00:03:05,458 --> 00:03:06,666
Yusuke…

42
00:03:13,750 --> 00:03:15,000
Nakamachi…

43
00:03:17,791 --> 00:03:19,125
Could it be?

44
00:03:32,708 --> 00:03:34,708
Oh, hey!

45
00:03:34,791 --> 00:03:35,916
Mr. Shinoda.

46
00:03:37,083 --> 00:03:37,958
What is it?

47
00:03:38,041 --> 00:03:39,875
Oh, nothing's wrong.

48
00:03:40,875 --> 00:03:42,708
Did you not get my call?

49
00:03:43,458 --> 00:03:45,458
Oh, I'm sorry.

50
00:03:46,166 --> 00:03:48,291
It's not a big deal, but…

51
00:03:48,375 --> 00:03:49,416
But what?

52
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:53,708
Did you

53
00:03:55,083 --> 00:03:56,125
get it working?

54
00:03:56,208 --> 00:03:57,041
Sure did.

55
00:03:58,250 --> 00:04:00,250
No way. That's incredible!

56
00:04:11,166 --> 00:04:13,666
That's a pretty nice sound.

57
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:15,375
Yeah, it sounds nice.

58
00:04:15,458 --> 00:04:18,375
I told you. Fate brought us here.

59
00:04:19,541 --> 00:04:22,583
It was waiting
for the day we'd finally meet.

60
00:04:24,375 --> 00:04:29,375
The rain cleared up too,
as if in celebration.

61
00:04:54,791 --> 00:04:55,708
Thank you.

62
00:04:57,916 --> 00:04:59,291
Please place those here.

63
00:05:02,583 --> 00:05:04,958
-I'll put these here too.
-Okay, thank you.

64
